"-" this means regular file
"d"  this means directory
"l" this means link
"c" this means special file
"s" this means socket
"p" this means named pipe
"b" this means block device


when we run ls -l we see like;

calvin@localhost:~$ ls -l
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 25 Feb 24 11:54 config
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 24 11:54 Desktop
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 25 Feb 24 11:54 Public
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 24 11:54 Videos
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 25 Feb 24 11:54 Pictures
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 25 Feb 24 11:54 Documents
